    "department": "Engineering \u0026 Product",
    "description": "ABOUT ELEVENLABS\n\nElevenLabs is an AI research and product company transforming how we interact with technology.\n\nWe launched in January 2023 with the first human-like AI voice model. Today, we serve millions of users and thousands of businesses - from fast-growing startups to large enterprises like Deutsche Telekom and Meta. Our investors are some of the world's most prominent, including Andreessen Horowitz, ICONIQ Growth and Sequoia. We've raised $781M in funding and our last valuation was $11B - multiples of 11, always.\n\nWe have expanded from voice into three main platforms:\n\n - ElevenAgents enables businesses to deliver seamless and intelligent customer experiences, with the integrations, testing, monitoring, and reliability necessary to deploy voice and chat agents at scale.\n\n - ElevenCreative empowers creators and marketers to generate and edit speech, music, image, and video across 70+ languages.\n\n - ElevenAPI gives developers access to our leading AI audio foundational models.\n\nEverything we do is the result of the creativity and commitment of our team - builders doing the best work of their lives. We are researchers, engineers, and operators. IOI medalists and ex-founders. If you want to work hard and create lasting positive impact, we want to hear from you.\n\n\nHOW WE WORK\n\n - High-velocity: Rapid experimentation, lean autonomous teams, and minimal bureaucracy.\n\n - Impact not job titles: We don’t have job titles. Instead, it’s about the impact you have. No task is above or beneath you.\n\n - AI first: We use AI to move faster with higher-quality results. We do this across the whole company—from engineering to growth to operations.\n\n - Excellence everywhere: Everything we do should match the quality of our AI models.\n\n - Global team: We prioritize your talent, not your location.\n\n\nWHAT WE OFFER\n\n - Innovative culture: You’ll be part of a generational opportunity to define the trajectory of AI, surrounded by a team pushing the boundaries of what’s possible.\n\n - Growth paths: Joining ElevenLabs means joining a dynamic team with countless opportunities to drive impact - beyond your immediate role and responsibilities.\n\n - Learning \u0026 development: ElevenLabs proactively supports professional development through an annual discretionary stipend.\n\n - Social travel: We also provide an annual discretionary stipend to meet up with colleagues each year, however you choose.\n\n - Annual company offsite: Each year, we bring the entire team together in a new location - past offsites have included Croatia and Italy.\n\n - Co-working: If you’re not located near one of our main hubs, we offer a monthly co-working stipend.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nAt ElevenLabs, we believe AI will fundamentally change how companies grow and win customers. As an AI Automations Engineer, you'll be at the heart of that transformation—designing and building the next generation of tooling for go-to-market (GTM), Operations, and Finance teams.\n\nThis is a highly cross-functional, technical role where you’ll use your full-stack engineering skills to build systems that supercharge ElevenLabs. You’ll embed within a specific team, and work closely with sales, marketing, operations, and product leaders to understand pain points, decompose ambiguous problems, and ship elegant, pragmatic solutions at speed.\n\nIf you’re the kind of person who treats every broken process as a challenge to be fixed with software—and if you get excited about how AI is reshaping sales and marketing—you’ll thrive in this role.\n\nAs an AI Automations Engineer, you can expect to:\n\n - Own the design and implementation of internal tools and infrastructure that directly support our revenue teams.\n\n - Build AI agents to automate processes, surface insights, and integrate data across multiple tools and resources.\n\n - Partner with strategy and operations teams to deeply understand the customer and sales lifecycle, then automate, optimize, and reimagine it with code.\n\n - Own \u0026 launch experiments to identify new ways to scale and optimize ElevenLabs operations, and drive their development and implementation.\n\n - Design and deliver technical enablement that makes insights actionable across the ElevenLabs teams, through education, tooling, and streamlined workflows.\n\n - Be a force multiplier: rapidly prototype and deploy full-stack features that have immediate business impact.\n\n\nREQUIREMENTS\n\nWe’re looking for exceptional engineers who are passionate about building technical systems that scale. You might be a technical start-up cofounder or a fullstack engineer who is dying to build more with AI. If this article https://thegtme.com/p/the-rise-of-the-gtm-engineer?inf_ver=2\u0026inf_ctx=BGwaaNA1_vQUfBE_7WSMpXh6zrGZXrF75znSn4KaU8gYiuwDSv-Qxu4sUnjU5_a__2vSRxb1-6fLRX9JFkFgfqti4_h_tO1AGdbAv1D5PnWH28Y8o0Ay5rwCwH-pB1v6wq1a0qLh7o1FPrHrmnpio-gf1RqS7NjsKaJPt-0KKxrtZnbz5O_21abCe1CfSanxXQfEdrfO5T-89ULbbCdm0FS20_U8QArShIdkrJEL6Gh_DLzlJi0HHUA_gsjouHMd2cGsIUq56duQ0ndyA4kz0xy-KfpyWMtUtuHVzlFd6tSLatB4AiG9P8rbK2Zqyr22h0f10R18po4NG4o0zFLpuA%3D%3D sounds fun to you, you’re probably a good fit.\n\n - Strong full-stack engineering skills: you’re comfortable moving across frontend, backend, and infrastructure as needed. Minimum requirements: Python, SQL.\n\n - Builder mindset: you move fast, work independently, and don't wait for perfect specs—you uncover them through action. You have a talent for spotting patterns, identifying opportunities to automate or standardize, and translating them into scalable solutions.\n\n - Deep product intuition: you think in terms of systems and workflows, and care about the business impact of what you build. You enjoy designing \u0026 building tools that empower internal teams to move faster and operate more independently.\n\n - Passionate about AI: you’re eager to explore how AI can transform B2B sales, marketing, operation, and finance. You have experience working with data, AI agents, LLMs, prompting, and common integration patterns across tools and systems.\n   \n\n\nLOCATION\n\nThis role is remote and can be executed globally. If you prefer, you can work from our offices in Bangalore, Dublin, London, New York, San Francisco, Tokyo, and Warsaw. Specific teams may have specific location preferences.\n\n#LI-Remote",
